e.g. For example, a term that appears say just 4 times in a corpus of say size 1000, will have a frequency of appearance of 0.004 =4/1000.

This term's sparsity will be (1000-4)/1000 = 1- 0.004 = 0.996 = 99.6%.

##Appendix function

clean.text = function(x)
{
  # tolower
  x = tolower(x)
  # remove rt
  x = gsub("rt", "", x)
  # remove at
  x = gsub("@\\w+", "", x)
  # remove punctuation
  x = gsub("[[:punct:]]", "", x)
  # remove numbers
  x = gsub("[[:digit:]]", "", x)
  # remove links http
  x = gsub("http\\w+", "", x)
  # remove tabs
  x = gsub("[ |\t]{2,}", "", x)
  # remove blank spaces at the beginning
  x = gsub("^ ", "", x)
  # remove blank spaces at the end
  x = gsub(" $", "", x)
  return(x)
}
